  "prompt": "What is the healthiest food I can snack on throughout the day? Must be fairly affordable + fairly tasty.",
  "response": "One of the healthiest snacks that meets your criteria of being affordable and fairly tasty is nuts and seeds, such as almonds, walnuts, or sunflower seeds. Here's why they make an excellent choice:\n\n1. **Nutritional Benefits**: Nuts and seeds are rich in healthy fats, protein, fiber, vitamins, and minerals. They support heart health, provide sustained energy, and help with satiety.\n\n2. **Affordability**: While some nuts can be expensive, buying in bulk or choosing more affordable options like sunflower seeds or peanuts can keep costs down.\n\n3. **Tastiness**: Nuts and seeds have a natural, satisfying flavor that can be enhanced with a light amount of seasoning, if desired. Roasting them can also bring out their flavor without adding unhealthy ingredients.\n\n4. **Convenience**: They are non-perishable and easy to portion out, making them a great on-the-go snack.\n\nTo add variety, you can mix them with dried fruits or dark chocolate chips for a trail mix, but be mindful of portion sizes to manage calorie intake.",
